The city's Fire and Rescue Services said the fire broke out just after 5 am on Monday morning; it is now extinguished. CAPE TOWN - Several homes have been destroyed in a fire at Green Point informal settlement in Khayelitsha. The city's Fire and Rescue Services said the fire broke out just after 5 am on Monday morning; the fire is now extinguished. The municipality says its Disaster Risk Management Centre is currently busy with assessments. The city's Jermaine Carlese said: “The response comprised of four fire engines, two water tank vehicles and a rescue vehicle. The fire was extinguished shortly after 7 am this morning and one adult male sustained minor injuries who was treated by the brigade. The cause of the fire is unknown.” (Edited by Mihlali Ntsabo)